From: r8q bring-up <r8q@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH] r8q: mfd: max77705: accept PASS2 silicon revision

The r8q (Galaxy S20 FE 5G) unit's MAX77705 companion PMIC reports silicon
revision PASS2 (PMICREV & 0x7 == 0x2), but mainline mfd/max77705.c only
whitelists PASS3 and bails with -ENODEV ("Rev.0x2 is not tested") on anything
else. The charger and fuel-gauge register layout is the same on PASS2 --
Samsung's downstream driver drives both revisions -- so accept PASS2 as well
and emit an info line noting it is untested. Verified: charger probes and the
battery charges (status "Charging", current positive) on a PASS2 r8q.
---
--- a/drivers/mfd/max77705.c
+++ b/drivers/mfd/max77705.c
@@ -105,8 +105,17 @@
 		return -ENODEV;

 	pmic_rev = pmic_rev_value & MAX77705_REVISION_MASK;
-	if (pmic_rev != MAX77705_PASS3)
+	/*
+	 * r8q (Galaxy S20 FE): this unit's MAX77705 reports PASS2 (rev 0x2),
+	 * but mainline only whitelisted PASS3. The charger/fuel-gauge register
+	 * layout is the same on PASS2 -- Samsung's downstream driver drives both
+	 * -- so accept PASS2 as well and just note it.
+	 */
+	if (pmic_rev != MAX77705_PASS3 && pmic_rev != MAX77705_PASS2)
 		return dev_err_probe(dev, -ENODEV, "Rev.0x%x is not tested\n", pmic_rev);
+	if (pmic_rev != MAX77705_PASS3)
+		dev_info(dev, "accepting untested MAX77705 rev 0x%x (PASS%d)\n",
+			 pmic_rev, pmic_rev);

 	/* Active Discharge Enable */
 	regmap_update_bits(max77705->regmap, MAX77705_PMIC_REG_MAINCTRL1, 1, 1);
